n Palestine and the Marxist faith in class struggle. Closely allied with this ideology was Yiddishism, a movement whose adherents envisioned the Yiddish language and culture, not religious tradition, as the unifying force of Jewish identity. We follow Tcherikower, Efroikin, and Kalmanovitch as they navigate the tumultuous early decades of the twentieth century in pursuit of a Jewish national renaissance in Eastern Europe. Correcting the misconception of Yiddishism as a radically secular movement, Karlip uncovers surprising confluences between Judaism and the avowedly nonreligious forms of Jewish nationalism. An essential contribution to Jewish historiography, The Tragedy of a Generation is a probing and poignant chronicle of lives shaped by ideological conviction and tested to the limits by historical crisis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aJewish nationalismzRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish socialistszRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszRussiaxIdentityxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszRussiaxIntellectual lifey20th century. 0aJewszRussiaxPolitics and governmenty20th century. 0aLabor ZionismzRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aYiddishistszRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 4aHISTORY / Europe / Russia & the Former Soviet Union. 4aHISTORY / Holocaust. 4aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Nationalism. 4aRELIGION / Judaism / General. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY  2013z978311031712108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS08iTitle is p